\parai{Transparency} speaks of the ability to reproduce or otherwise understand how and why information is returned with respect to the base corpus. KGs are transparent, where the results provided for a query can be explained 
 in terms of their derivation steps and (where available) underlying data provenance.
 SEs are also transparent, though some aspects, like ranking algorithms, may be more opaque. LLMs, as black-box models, are largely opaque, meaning that it is difficult to understand how or why they generate particular responses, or what sources were used.